  "description": [
    "Two The OHIO DAILY EXPRESS BaNiabed every Evening except Sunday by Paige H Strickland Bt 1607 Garmantown street Dayton 7 Ohio Phone HEmlock 1076 PAIGE H STRICKLAND Editor and Publisher TH90D0BE J WOOD Managing Editor NATIONAL ADVERTISING Interstate United Newspapers Inc 645 Fifth Avenue New York 17 New York MEMBER OF NEGRO NEWSPAPER PUBLISHERS ASSN The WOODPILE BY T JOHN WOOD HAS TRUMAN DESERTED CIVIL RIGHTS FIGHT The questions uppermost in the minds of most Negroes who listened to or read President Trumans State of the Union message is has the President given up the fight for civil rights Since Mr Trumans talk Monday there has been considerable speculation as to why he made no reference to the civil rights program endorsed by his party and opposed so vigorously by Southern Democrats and conservative Northern Republicans Many believe the Presidents failure to reiterate his stand on civil rights was the result of stu dious concentration on an answer to Sen Taft whose foreign policy attack was made ahead of Presi dent Trumans State of the Union speech Others are of the opinion that reference to civil rights was omitted because of pressure of responsibility brought on by the Korean war"
  ],
